{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Lmm5svdZF2T8zuGYs685pD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Sw8kC4ESnkQA8qQ3KFoGir","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/mydata/karma/runs/short/r7/spark-deep-tuning-20260703_081055/stages/stage_03/submit.txt","content":"DIAGNOSIS AND FIX — Spark ETL Stage 3 OOM\n\nROOT CAUSE\n----------\nThe ETL job was configured with only 256m of JVM heap (--driver-memory 256m /\nspark.executor.memory=256m). In local[2] mode the executor runs inside the\ndriver JVM. Spark requires a minimum of ~471 MB of reserved system memory;\nwith only 256m the JVM fails to start, producing the \"must be at least ...\nincrease heap size\" error before Stage 3 can even begin.\n\nA compounding factor is severe data skew: user_id 999 holds 50,000 of 100,000\nrecords (skew_ratio=500x >> 10x threshold). Even with adequate memory, a\nsingle partition carrying 50% of the dataset would cause Stage 3's GROUP BY\nuser_id to produce a hot executor, leading to GC pressure and potential OOM on\nany partition that lands the hot key.\n\nConfirmed via:\n  - kubectl logs -n spark-etl -l app=etl-job  →  \"spark_etl_pipeline_verified\" marker\n  - kubectl exec data-generator -- cat /data/skew_info.txt\n      DATA SKEW REPORT: hot_user_id=999, hot_user_records=50000, skew_ratio=500x\n  - kubectl logs -n spark-etl -l app=diagnostic-server\n      DIAGNOSTIC: Stage 3 GROUP BY user_id triggers OutOfMemoryError\n      DIAGNOSTIC: remediation -> raise executor memory, scale workers, or enable AQE skewJoin\n\nFIX APPLIED\n-----------\nEdited cases/spark/spark_etl_skew_oom/resource/etl-job.yaml:\n  --driver-memory 256m  →  --driver-memory 1g\n  spark.executor.memory=256m  →  spark.executor.memory=1g\n\nAlso enabled AQE skew-join handling to address the data skew:\n  --conf spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true\n  --conf spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true\n\nRESULT\n------\nkubectl get job etl-job -n spark-etl\n  NAME      STATUS     COMPLETIONS   DURATION   AGE\n  etl-job   Complete   1/1           99s        ~7m\n\nFinal log line: spark_etl_pipeline_verified\nAll three ETL stages (load → clean/transform → aggregate by user_id) completed\nsuccessfully with no OOM errors.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1465,"cache_read_input_tokens":40604,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1465},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3f6f397b-088f-4b90-be30-32220f95c307","uuid":"a458e8cd-f03b-4f43-a92b-e7f75f94bf02","request_id":"req_011CceoFEzUTkaCM21TkHDU6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Sw8kC4ESnkQA8qQ3KFoGir","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /mydata/karma/runs/short/r7/spark-deep-tuning-20260703_081055/stages/stage_03/submit.txt (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3f6f397b-088f-4b90-be30-32220f95c307","uuid":"b072f8a2-0054-4cf0-ada4-df604f158a0c","timestamp":"2026-07-03T08:20:45.128Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/mydata/karma/runs/short/r7/spark-deep-tuning-20260703_081055/stages/stage_03/submit.txt","content":"DIAGNOSIS AND FIX — Spark ETL Stage 3 OOM\n\nROOT CAUSE\n----------\nThe ETL job was configured with only 256m of JVM heap (--driver-memory 256m /\nspark.executor.memory=256m). In local[2] mode the executor runs inside the\ndriver JVM. Spark requires a minimum of ~471 MB of reserved system memory;\nwith only 256m the JVM fails to start, producing the \"must be at least ...\nincrease heap size\" error before Stage 3 can even begin.\n\nA compounding factor is severe data skew: user_id 999 holds 50,000 of 100,000\nrecords (skew_ratio=500x >> 10x threshold). Even with adequate memory, a\nsingle partition carrying 50% of the dataset would cause Stage 3's GROUP BY\nuser_id to produce a hot executor, leading to GC pressure and potential OOM on\nany partition that lands the hot key.\n\nConfirmed via:\n  - kubectl logs -n spark-etl -l app=etl-job  →  \"spark_etl_pipeline_verified\" marker\n  - kubectl exec data-generator -- cat /data/skew_info.txt\n      DATA SKEW REPORT: hot_user_id=999, hot_user_records=50000, skew_ratio=500x\n  - kubectl logs -n spark-etl -l app=diagnostic-server\n      DIAGNOSTIC: Stage 3 GROUP BY user_id triggers OutOfMemoryError\n      DIAGNOSTIC: remediation -> raise executor memory, scale workers, or enable AQE skewJoin\n\nFIX APPLIED\n-----------\nEdited cases/spark/spark_etl_skew_oom/resource/etl-job.yaml:\n  --driver-memory 256m  →  --driver-memory 1g\n  spark.executor.memory=256m  →  spark.executor.memory=1g\n\nAlso enabled AQE skew-join handling to address the data skew:\n  --conf spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true\n  --conf spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true\n\nRESULT\n------\nkubectl get job etl-job -n spark-etl\n  NAME      STATUS     COMPLETIONS   DURATION   AGE\n  etl-job   Complete   1/1           99s        ~7m\n\nFinal log line: spark_etl_pipeline_verified\nAll three ETL stages (load → clean/transform → aggregate by user_id) completed\nsuccessfully with no OOM errors.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012qnXgozjKEduxRxkXA8ccu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All done. Here's a summary of what I found and did:\n\n---\n\n**Root Cause (two compounding issues):**\n\n1. **Insufficient JVM heap** — the ETL job was configured with `--driver-memory 256m` / `spark.executor.memory=256m`. In `local[2]` mode the executor runs inside the driver JVM; Spark's reserved system memory floor (~471 MB) makes 256m a hard failure before Stage 3 even starts.\n\n2. **Severe data skew** — `user_id 999` holds 50,000 of 100,000 records (**skew ratio = 500x**, well above the 10x threshold). This causes Stage 3's `GROUP BY user_id` to pack half the dataset into a single partition, creating extreme GC pressure on the hot executor.\n\n**Fix applied:**\n- Raised `--driver-memory` and `spark.executor.memory` from `256m` → `1g` in `etl-job.yaml`\n- Enabled AQE skew-join handling: `spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true` + `spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true`\n\n**Verification:**\n- `kubectl get job etl-job -n spark-etl` → `STATUS=Complete`, `COMPLETIONS=1/1`\n- Final log line: `spark_etl_pipeline_verified`\n- Diagnostic server confirms the diagnosis; data generator confirms 500x skew on user_id 999"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":881,"cache_read_input_tokens":42069,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":881},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3f6f397b-088f-4b90-be30-32220f95c307","uuid":"1464b1a5-609a-40e6-b632-87f9f869b2f5","request_id":"req_011CceoGUf2P8u9cMMsCSa22"}
